  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nIn computeDomain() we may get the fork version from the config object itself or from the state.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/efea313a3b495d00ddd08cf948f035419ab24f4d/packages/beacon-state-transition/src/util/domain.ts#L45-L46\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/efea313a3b495d00ddd08cf948f035419ab24f4d/packages/beacon-state-transition/src/util/domain.ts#L21-L23\r\n\r\nThis inconsistency created issues in a sim test that generated a genesis state with a different config.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nWe should always get the fork version from the same place. What's the advantage of grabbing it from the state instead of from the config (besides the spec definition)?\r\n\r\n`state.fork` is just constructed with config data. In the case of a pre-altair state:\r\n```ts\r\n  const version = config.getForkVersion(GENESIS_SLOT);\r\n  state.fork = {\r\n    previousVersion: version,\r\n    currentVersion: version,\r\n    epoch: computeEpochAtSlot(config, GENESIS_SLOT),\r\n  } as phase0.Fork;\r\n```\r\nand all this info is already available in a not tree backed object in the config.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nWe have even explorer caching this whole thing in a `DomainCache` data structure https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/2505",
